# SupAgentic — Pull & Combine 7 AI Tool Repos

Pull all 7 open-source AI tools from the Fireship video into `c:\Users\OMEN\Documents\SupAgentic` as a unified project.

## Repositories to Clone

| # | Tool | GitHub Repo | Description |
|---|------|-------------|-------------|
| 1 | The Agency | `msitarzewski/agency-agents` | AI agent personality collection |
| 2 | Promptfoo | `promptfoo/promptfoo` | LLM evaluation & red-teaming CLI |
| 3 | MiroFish | `666ghj/MiroFish` | Swarm intelligence prediction engine |
| 4 | Impeccable | `pbakaus/impeccable` | Frontend design prompting skill for Claude |
| 5 | OpenViking | `volcengine/OpenViking` | Context database for AI agents |
| 6 | Heretic | `p-e-w/heretic` | Model abliteration / uncensoring tool |
| 7 | NanoChat | `karpathy/nanochat` | Minimal SLM training framework |

## Proposed Structure

```
SupAgentic/
├── README.md                  # Unified project overview
├── tools/
│   ├── agency-agents/         # git clone of The Agency
│   ├── promptfoo/             # git clone of Promptfoo
│   ├── mirofish/              # git clone of MiroFish
│   ├── impeccable/            # git clone of Impeccable
│   ├── openviking/            # git clone of OpenViking
│   ├── heretic/               # git clone of Heretic
│   └── nanochat/              # git clone of NanoChat
└── index.html                 # Visual dashboard / launcher page
```

## Proposed Changes

### SupAgentic Root

#### [NEW] [README.md](file:///c:/Users/OMEN/Documents/SupAgentic/README.md)
Unified README covering all 7 tools — what each does, links to each repo, and how to get started.

#### [NEW] [index.html](file:///c:/Users/OMEN/Documents/SupAgentic/index.html)
A sleek single-page dashboard with cards for each tool, showing name, description, category, and links to their respective directories and GitHub pages.

#### [NEW] [tools/](file:///c:/Users/OMEN/Documents/SupAgentic/tools/)
Each of the 7 repos cloned as subdirectories inside `tools/`.

## Execution Steps

1. Create the `tools/` directory
2. `git clone` each of the 7 repos into `tools/`
3. Create `README.md` with the unified project overview
4. Create `index.html` as a visual dashboard
5. Verify all clones succeeded and directory structure is correct

## Verification Plan

### Automated Verification
- Run `dir tools\` to confirm all 7 subdirectories exist
- Run `git -C tools\<each-repo> log -1` to confirm each is a valid git repo with commit history

### Manual Verification
- Open `index.html` in the browser to verify the dashboard renders correctly with all 7 tool cards
